.Dd April 8, 2025
.Dt BITNETD 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm bitnetd
.Nd BitNet LLM inference daemon
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Op Fl f
.Op Fl t
.Op Fl v
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a Unix daemon that serves BitNet 1-bit LLM inference over HTTP,
exposing an OpenAI-compatible REST API.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c Ar config
Specify the configuration file.
Default is
.Pa /etc/bitnetd.conf .
.It Fl f
Run in foreground mode.
Do not daemonize; log to stderr.
.It Fl t
Test configuration file syntax and exit.
.It Fl v
Print version and exit.
.El
.Sh SIGNALS
.Bl -tag -width "SIGUSR1"
.It Dv SIGHUP
Reload configuration file.
.It Dv SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown.
.It Dv SIGINT
Same as SIGTERM.
.It Dv SIGUSR1
Reopen log files (for log rotation).
.It Dv SIGUSR2
Dump status information to log.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/var/run/bitnetd.pid"
.It Pa /etc/bitnetd.conf
Default configuration file.
.It Pa /var/run/bitnetd.pid
PID file.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr bitnetd.conf 5 ,
.Xr bitnetctl 1
